Thanks again for doing this, and also to @erdOne for helping with review.

Thanks so much for doing this. Awesome work!

A few last tiny suggestions.

bors d+

```suggestion
The coefficients of the characteristic polynomials of a linear family of endomorphisms
```
Can we easily remove this `erw`? (Not essential.)
Done.
Is it possible to move it?
Agreed: we should move this (and generalise to `M →ₗ[R] N`).
Done
Maybe mention that they are finite free?
Done
I wonder if it is useful to package `polyCharpoly φ b (Module.Free.chooseBasis R M)` into a new function so that the user won't need to obtain a basis before using this?
I agree with @erdOne . I would rename this to `polyCharpolyAux` and then once `polyCharpolyAux_basisIndep` has been proved, define a new `polyCharpoly` that invokes `Module.Free.chooseBasis R M`.
Done
First time I've seen this neat `if ... then ... else` pattern: neat!
Thanks

I think this makes it slightly clearer what the issue is:
```suggestion
def «end» (b : Basis ι R M) : Basis (ι × ι) R (Module.End R M) :=
```

True, I considered it, but otoh didn't really like the french quotes. I don't think it is well-known to non-experts what they do. The current name follows a more widely used pattern.
Do you have a strong preference?
No strong preference, let's leave this alone then!

Am I right in thinking that we don't have the basis for linear maps? If so, how about:
```suggestion
variable {R M ι : Type*} [CommRing R] [AddCommGroup M] [Module R M] [Fintype ι] [DecidableEq ι]
  {ι' M' : Type*} [AddCommGroup M'] [Module R M'] [Fintype ι'] [DecidableEq ι']

def linearMap (b : Basis ι R M) (b' : Basis ι' R M') : Basis (ι' × ι) R (M →ₗ[R] M') :=
  (Matrix.stdBasis R ι' ι).map (LinearMap.toMatrix b b').symm
```
and `end` below can be an `abbrev` or even maybe absent?
Fixed. I opted to have the abbrev, and copy the tiny API. I think it aids discoverability and readability in applications. Also, `b.end` is a bit shorter than `b.linearMap b`.

```suggestion
```
I added this comment to explain why I do not let `simps` generate the lemma: the linter complains.

How about we support `M →ₗ[R] N` and not just `Module.End R M`:
```suggestion
See `TensorProductEnd` for the case `N = M`, bundled as `A`-algebra homomorphism. -/
@[simps!]
noncomputable
def TensorProductₗ (N : Type*) [AddCommGroup N] [Module R N] :
    A ⊗[R] (M →ₗ[R] N) →ₗ[A] A ⊗[R] M →ₗ[A] A ⊗[R] N :=
  TensorProduct.AlgebraTensorModule.lift <|
  { toFun := fun a ↦ a • baseChangeHom R A M N
```

(This could probably be a one-liner if `TensorProduct.AlgebraTensorModule.lift` was generalised to be a linear map rather than just a raw function, but I don't think we should tackle this as part of this work.)
Thanks, I made the generalization. And yes, let's postpone that other refactor of `TensorProduct.AlgebraTensorModule.lift`.
This line looks like is has gone astray (I guess either drop it or move it up two lines and ident).
I think a short `## Imlementation details` section would be useful here to outline the clever technique used to establish independence on choice of basis.
Done

**[imports]** reported by [reviewdog](https://github.com/reviewdog/reviewdog) :dog:
```suggestion ```

```suggestion
open LinearMap in
lemma _root_.Basis.baseChange_linearMap [Fintype ι] [DecidableEq ι]
    {ι' N : Type*} [Fintype ι'] [DecidableEq ι'] [AddCommMonoid N] [Module R N]
    (A : Type*) [CommSemiring A] [Algebra R A] (b : Basis ι R M) (b' : Basis ι' R N) (ij : ι × ι') :
    baseChange A (b'.linearMap b ij) = (basis A b').linearMap (basis A b) ij := by
  apply (basis A b').ext
  intro k
  conv_lhs => simp only [basis_apply, baseChange_tmul]
  simp_rw [Basis.linearMap_apply_apply, basis_apply]
  split <;> simp only [TensorProduct.tmul_zero]

open LinearMap in
lemma _root_.Basis.baseChange_end [Fintype ι] [DecidableEq ι]
    (A : Type*) [CommSemiring A] [Algebra R A] (b : Basis ι R M) (ij : ι × ι) :
    baseChange A (b.end ij) = (basis A b).end ij :=
  b.baseChange_linearMap A b ij
```
(maybe worth a `BaseChange` section to share variables and `open LinearMap`)

We actually already have this (with slightly weaker assumptions) as [Module.Finite.base_change](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/RingTheory/Finiteness.html#Module.Finite.base_change)
```suggestion
```

```suggestion
See `LinearMap.tensorProductEnd` for this map specialized to endomorphisms,
```

I think we should regard `polyCharpolyAux` as a pure implementation detail and never expose it to the user so this lemma should probably be:
```suggestion
lemma polyCharpoly_eq_of_basis [DecidableEq ιM] (bₘ : Basis ιM R M) :
    polyCharpoly φ b =
    (charpoly.univ R ιM).map (MvPolynomial.bind₁ (φ.toMvPolynomial b bₘ.end)) := by
  rw [polyCharpoly, φ.polyCharpolyAux_basisIndep b (Module.Free.chooseBasis R M) bₘ,
    polyCharpolyAux]
```

```suggestion
    [CommSemiring R] [AddCommMonoid M] [Module R M] [Module.Free R M]
```
